theorem Topology.interior_closure_union_closure_compl_eq_univ
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    interior (closure A) ∪ closure (Aᶜ) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
  classical
  -- We prove that every point `x : X` belongs to the left-hand side.
  ext x
  constructor
  · intro _; simp
  · intro _
    by_cases h_cl : x ∈ closure (Aᶜ)
    · exact Or.inr h_cl
    · -- If `x ∉ closure (Aᶜ)`, then `x ∈ interior A`, hence in `interior (closure A)`.
      have h_mem_compl : x ∈ (closure (Aᶜ) : Set X)ᶜ := by
        simpa [Set.mem_compl, h_cl]
      have h_intA : x ∈ interior A := by
        -- `interior A = (closure (Aᶜ))ᶜ`
        have h_eq :=
          Topology.interior_eq_compl_closure_compl (X := X) (A := A)
        simpa [h_eq] using h_mem_compl
      have h_intClA : x ∈ interior (closure A) :=
        (Topology.interior_subset_interior_closure (X := X) (A := A)) h_intA
      exact Or.inl h_intClA

theorem Topology.interior_inter_subset {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    interior (A ∩ B) ⊆ interior A ∩ interior B := by
  intro x hx
  have hxA : x ∈ interior A :=
    (interior_mono (Set.inter_subset_left : (A ∩ B) ⊆ A)) hx
  have hxB : x ∈ interior B :=
    (interior_mono (Set.inter_subset_right : (A ∩ B) ⊆ B)) hx
  exact And.intro hxA hxB
